          "Authors propose a new attention-based model to predict student performance on OULAD. This model, named AML creates an Attention Layer from the LMS logs. \n\nAs time moves forward, so does the predictive capability of the model - past week 15 AML outperforms all benchmarks",
          "  • course information, students’ pre-course learning conditions, and timing of classroom test submissions not used\n\n  • Weak cold start scenario\n\n  • Results are not impressive vs baselines\n\n  • Only uses OULAD\n\n  • No interpretation of “interpretability” benefits \n\n  • Feature set undisclosed   "
